Spot Silver Tumbles as Much as 3% in London After Rally to All-Time High

-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-04-25T14:32:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/spot-silver-tumbles-as-much-as-3-in-london-after-rally-to-all-time-high.html
Silver for immediately delivery
fell $1.1025, or 2.3 percent, to $46.1475 an ounce at 10:28 a.m.
 New York  time. Earlier, the metal rose to a record $49.79.  On the Comex in New York, silver futures for May delivery
rose 20.3 cents, or 0.4 percent, to $46.28. The metal had
dropped as much as 0.9 percent after surging as much as 8.2
percent to $49.845.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
